post_text: Today we would like to take a moment to commemorate the lives of those who died in the 2001 terrorist attacks on the World Trade Center in New York City and the Pentagon in Virginia and those who perished when the hijacked United Airlines Flight 93 crashed in Pennsylvania. We continue to honor the heroism and bravery of those first responders, including firefighters, law enforcement officials, and civilians who worked to save the lives of others. Today we are incredibly grateful for their selfless service. We will always remember September 11, 2001.

post_text:
We are hosting an In-Person parent training night for Remote Parents Only.

We will provide hands-on training to assist parents with some of the most common technical issues associated with remote learning. We will discuss Zoom, Canvas, Classlink, and Connectivity.

We want parents to bring your student's device so that you can show us issues that you are having at home or try out the platforms while we are there to help. We are offering this training on Two Nights to try to accommodate all parents.

The first offering will be Thursday, Sept 10, at 6:00 pm in the Intermediate Cafeteria.
The second offering will be Monday, Sept 14, at 6:00 pm in the Intermediate Cafeteria.

Parents will be required to wear a mask and be social distancing between families.

post_text: SHAC is hosting an Anti-Vape Poster Contest!
shared_text:
Navarro ISD - Student Health Advisory Council - SHAC
September 2 at 7:23 AM ·

SHAC is hosting an Anti-Vape Poster Contest

Turn in your post to your school nurse by September 14th!

The CDC webpage states that vaping nicotine is “highly addictive and can harm adolescent brain development, which continues into the early to mid-20s”.

Rules
- The poster must be in between 8.5 x 11 to 18 x 24 inches
- Upon completion, the poster must be flat and able to be copied
- The poster must be original work by the artist(s)
- Any Inappropriate, demeaning, or controversial posters will not be allowed
- Judges will be contest nonparticipants at the Sept 15th SHAC meeting
- Extra consideration for school pride

Prizes (One Winner Per Grade)
- High School - $100 Visa
- Junior High - $20 Sonic, $25 Tipsy Cow, $15 On The Grind
- Intermediate - $20 Tipsy Cow, $25 Kriby’s gift card

The winning posters will be chosen on September 15th and will also be displayed in your school hallways

post_text:
La Transferencia Electrónica de Beneficios por Pandemia (P-EBT, por sus siglas en inglés) es un beneficio de alimentos único para las familias que perdieron el acceso a comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido debido al cierre de las escuelas. A fin de mayo, las escuelas les enviarán instrucciones para realizar una solicitud a las familias elegibles para la P-EBT. La solicitud de la P-EBT estará disponible la primera semana de junio.
Los beneficios de alimentos de la P-EBT son para los niños que recibieron beneficios de alimentos del Programa Asistencial de Nutrición Suplementaria (SNAP, por sus siglas en inglés) para marzo de 2020 y para los niños que estén certificados para recibir comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido en Texas durante el año escolar 2019-20. Para obtener más información, visite: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT
text:
La Transferencia Electrónica de Beneficios por Pandemia (P-EBT, por sus siglas en inglés) es un beneficio de alimentos único para las familias que perdieron el acceso a comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido debido al cierre de las escuelas. A fin de mayo, las escuelas les enviarán instrucciones para realizar una solicitud a las familias elegibles para la P-EBT. La solicitud de la P-EBT estará disponible la primera semana de junio.
Los beneficios de alimentos de la P-EBT son para los niños que recibieron beneficios de alimentos del Programa Asistencial de Nutrición Suplementaria (SNAP, por sus siglas en inglés) para marzo de 2020 y para los niños que estén certificados para recibir comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido en Texas durante el año escolar 2019-20. Para obtener más información, visite: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text: The Navarro ISD Board of Trustees voted unanimously to hire Mrs. Wendi Russell as Superintendent of Schools at the Special meeting held on Tuesday, May 5. Mrs. Russell was offered a three year contract that will begin May 28. Mrs. Russell has experience with the challenges of a growing school District, and she is looking forward to developing meaningful relationships with staff, students, parents and community. She said that her vision is “to build on the dynamic education and extracurricular activities that Navarro ISD is known for.”
text: The Navarro ISD Board of Trustees voted unanimously to hire Mrs. Wendi Russell as Superintendent of Schools at the Special meeting held on Tuesday, May 5. Mrs. Russell was offered a three year contract that will begin May 28. Mrs. Russell has experience with the challenges of a growing school District, and she is looking forward to developing meaningful relationships with staff, students, parents and community. She said that her vision is “to build on the dynamic education and extracurricular activities that Navarro ISD is known for.”

Due to the school closures, the Navarro ISD Child Nutrition Department announces that we will offer free curbside meals Monday, March 16th thru Friday, March 20th at the Navarro Intermediate Cafeteria. Meals will be distributed on the west side of the cafeteria.

The to go meals will be available from 11 am to 12:30 pm each day. Each meal will include lunch and a next day breakfast.

Navarro ISD will issue meals to any Navarro student that is 18 years and younger. Adults that are accompanying children must have their child present in order to receive a meal.

Our staff has taken great protective measures to ensure that sanitation and safety is our number one priority. We look forward to serving your students during this time of need. If you have any questions or concerns you may reach us via email at carlette.drabek@nisd.us.

Please see the attached invitation to the Navarro ISD Veterans Day program on Monday, November 11 at 8:30 A.M. at Erwin-Lee Field. We would be honored to have local veterans, elected officials, and area organizations join us in this district-wide event.

Veterans and officials may enter the stadium at the south, north, or west gate and be seated on the field.

post_text:
Child Development Screenings

Do you have a 3 to 5 year old child? Do you think he or she is growing and developing like other children of the same age?

Navarro ISD is responsible for evaluating and identifying children who may require special education services and for providing those services to children ages 3 and older. As part of this process, our staff is offering free developmental screenings for children ages 3 to 5 who reside within our district boundaries. Developmental areas included in the screening are language, learning, motor, vision, and hearing.

Screenings will be offered at Navarro Elementary School on Tuesday, November 5th from 9 am to 11 am and Thursday, November 7th from 5 pm to 6:30 pm. Please contact Jennifer Reinhard at 830-372-1933 for an appointment.

We will be combining a few bus routes, due to a current shortage of drivers. We hope that this situation will resolve soon. In the meantime, please be aware of the following—

Bus 15 will not run.

• Junior High and High School students who live in Continental will ride Bus 7.

• Junior High and High School students who live in Geronimo Haven will ride Bus 11.

• Students of all grades who live on Glenewinkel Road will ride Bus 8.

Bus 21 will not run.

Students of all grades who live in Elm Grove will ride Bus 12. If Bus 12 becomes full, Bus 14 or Bus 18 will follow shortly.

7th grade students in Mill Creek Crossing and the Village at Mill Creek will ride Bus 19, 20, or 16.

All other routes will operate on the same schedule as last year.

post_text:
During the month of October, the Texas Department of Agriculture (TDA) hosts the annual Farm Fresh Challenge. The Challenge is a fun and engaging way for school nutrition professionals and their schools to gain recognition for their efforts to bring local foods and garden-based learning activities to their students.

Navarro ISD participated in the Farm Fresh Challenge during the month of October then continued to serve Farm Fresh on other days but especially on Fridays for most of the year. We offered items like milk, bread and fresh produce items which are locally sourced from Texas producers.

On June 13, 2019, Navarro ISD was recognized for the Best of the Bunch Award for participating in the challenge by the Department of Agriculture. This is the fifth year for Navarro ISD to receive this award.

Carlette Drabek, Navarro ISD Food Service Director, accepted the award for the district.

811 - Know What's Below - Texas School Pipeline Safety - Energy sources like gas and other petroleum products are transported through underground pipelines. During Spring and Summer, digging activity such as landscaping and construction projects increase damage risks.

If you suspect a leak inside or outside of your home, avoid anything that could create a spark, leave the area by foot, warn others to stay away and call 911.
Do not re-enter the area until emergency responders have informed you that it is safe to do so.
www.texas811.org http://edl.io/n1031090

The Gifted and Talented program referral period is open from March 18 - April 12. - Gifted and Talented referrals for students from all grade levels.

Dear Parents,

You may be aware of what appears to be increasing efforts to infiltrate children’s programs with dangerous and disturbing messages.

There are numerous reports that, in an effort to avoid adult detection, the "Momo Challenge" appears in the middle of child programs in social media and video games, such as Facebook, Kids YouTube, WhatsApp, Peppa Pig, Fortnight, and Minecraft encouraging children to commit dangerous and potentially violent acts.

Momo is a ghoulish-looking avatar that has threatened and cyberbullied children across the world. If children refuse to do the "challenge", Momo threatens to leak personal information, leaves disturbing messages, and sends violent images to the child.

Some of the information above may not be accurate, or it may be exaggerated, but I want parents to be aware of the possibility, so that you can protect your children.

Surgeon General’s Advisory on E-cigarette Use Among Youth - The E-cigarette Epidemic Among Youth - Dear Parents:

The Surgeon General of the United States has published an important
message about teenage use of electronic cigarettes. In an effort to discourage students from engaging in an unhealthy and potentially dangerous practice, we have elevated the consequence for using, giving, possessing or selling e-cigarettes. A student who engages in this activity at school or at a school related activity, may be placed
in the Disciplinary Alternative School. (See the Student Code of Conduct
on the campus website). The most common device, and the easiest to hide,
is the JUUL. Parents, please be aware that many young people are engaging
in "Juuling," believing that it is relatively harmless.

More information can be found at https://e-cigarettes.surgeongeneral.gov/default.htm http://edl.io/n976899

post_text:
Surgeon General’s Advisory on E-cigarette Use Among Youth - The E-cigarette Epidemic Among Youth

KNOW THE RISKS. TAKE ACTION. PROTECT OUR KIDS.

You Can Take Action
We must take aggressive steps to protect our children from these highly potent products that risk exposing a new generation of young people to nicotine. The bad news is that e-cigarette use has become an epidemic among our nation’s young people. However, the good news is that we know what works to effectively protect our kids from all forms of tobacco product use, including e-cigarettes. We must now apply these strategies to e-cigarettes, including USB flash drive shaped products such as JUUL. To achieve success, we must work together, aligning and coordinating efforts across both old and new partners at the national, state, and local levels. Everyone can play an important role in protecting our nation’s young people from the risks of e-cigarettes.

Click on the link to access more information on how you can help.
https://e-cigarettes.surgeongeneral.gov/default.htm
http://edl.io/n976899

Navarro FFA
December 1, 2018 at 4:15 PM ·

At the beginning of November 455 FFA members across the state of Texas competed at their respective District level contests. Mid-November the top 2 from each District competed in their respective Area level contests. Yesterday the top 2 from each of Texas FFA’s 12 Areas competed in the Preliminary Round of the Texas FFA State Contest. Today the top 10 from the preliminary round competed in the Finals Round of the Texas FFA State Contest.

In FFA our levels of competition are broken up by geographical location, not school size. Which means our Navarro FFA students compete against schools that range from the smallest 1A to the largest 6A.

And, after all was said and done for this year’s round of Leadership Development Events (LDEs), Aschlen finished 8th out of the Top 10 FFA Job Interview contestants in Texas!!!
Way to go Aschlen!!!

#TexasFFAStateLDEs2018
#JobInterviewTop10

post_text:
To our Navarro community,

We are saddened by the death of one of our own, Oliver Soria. The loss of this member of our school community is a very difficult time for us all. A variety of emotions is a normal response to any loss, and Oliver’s family has shared their wishes that Navarro be comforted through this loss. At this time we ask that you respect Oliver’s family and allow them time to heal privately. We have counselors available to help you process your feelings. If you’d like to speak to a counselor, please let your teacher know. At this time we ask that you keep Oliver and his family in your prayers.
text:
To our Navarro community,

We are saddened by the death of one of our own, Oliver Soria. The loss of this member of our school community is a very difficult time for us all. A variety of emotions is a normal response to any loss, and Oliver’s family has shared their wishes that Navarro be comforted through this loss. At this time we ask that you respect Oliver’s family and allow them time to heal privately. We have counselors available to help you process your feelings. If you’d like to speak to a counselor, please let your teacher know. At this time we ask that you keep Oliver and his family in your prayers.
